      "role": "user",
      "content": "the idea of a wrapper seems doable. i'm mostly worried about these leaks being really insidious—like, they're tiny, they happen in weird edge cases, and they just hide in the background until the system is already failing. how can i differentiate between a legitimate spike in usage and one of those little hidden errors that just slowly eats away at the heap?",
